pros:
-Cisco puts a lot of effort into hiring a certain type of people that represent the company's culture and this shows on a daily basis, very helpful team;
-Well established company, many processes are in place, there is a lot of information and experts to help guide you;
-if you like to not just be involved with your role activities but also on volunteer work or other internal initiatives that allow you to share your passion or learn new skills to  perhaps make a move to a new role, this is definitely possible here. I do it and I love it
-  I work mainly from the office but I have family in other countries so I can work remotely. When I travel for work, I also try to stay longer on my own, to visit, and I work from hostels or anywhere;
-benefits: meal debit card for restaurants, transportation debit card for gas or bicycle gear,  on our birthday the company gives us a day off (which can be taken when we want, for example to do a long weekend).

1) The company gives you a lot but also request a lot;
2) Opportunity for working directly with Customer;
3) Trainings available for everyone who want to develop;
4) Really BIG brand;
5) Very good benefits;
6) No processes and procedures how to perform the work, what is sometimes also some kind of Cons unfortunately;
7) Beeing close to management regardless the level;
8) High working culture;
9) Working with seniors;
10) Working with passionates;
11) Time2Give activities.

cons:
1) Flexible hours - it is hard to decide what calls you need to decline and IF to decline any (at the evenings for example)...
2) No processes and procedures how to perform the work;
3) No company cars for all senior roles;
4) Salary could be higher.

pros:
- Wide products portfolio;
- Very well-known brand, easy to speak with customers;
- Always very innovative - and a step ahead of any competitors, do what clients need for business;
- Flexible work schedule, work from home is ok if you do your job good;
- Great salary and benefits (bonus);
- Easy to track your performance, managers are ready to help you if you need any support;
- Great team - everybody like a big family, great climate! 
Great office, very good technical gear (Apple, Lenovo);
-

cons:
- High load and not always can to find good work\life balance;
- Some roles (AM) may include a number of business trips - be prepared;
- You should live by Policy (a number of them) - so be careful with that - important moment!
- A big number of internal product trainings, you should remember a lot of moments to sell good.
